ck -- tA Moment of Truth -- tThe Future -- tThe Gallows -- tThe Winds of Change -- tThe Breeze of Youth -- tA Successful Woman -- tIn Need of Reassurance -- tShort and Sassy -- tThe Collapse of Barriers -- tThe Beginning -- tA Moment of Contemplation -- tI Will Try Tomorrow -- tNotes -- tAbout the Authors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aConsisting of sixty short stories by forty women writers from across the Arab world, this collection opens numerous windows onto Arab culture and society and offers keen insights into what Arab women feel and think. The stories deal not only with feminist issues but also with topics of a social, cultural, and political nature. Different styles and modes of writing are represented, along with a diversity of techniques and creative approaches, and the authors present many points of view and various ways of solving problems and confronting situations in everyday life. Lively, outspoken, and provocative, these stories are essential reading for anyone interested in the Arab world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aArabic fictionxWomen authorsvTranslations into English. 0aShort stories, ArabicvTranslations into English. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Fiction. 4aLiterature : Arab Literature. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aAbdallah, Sufi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmin, Nura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAshour, Radwa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAt’ut, Samiya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzzam, Samira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBakr, Salwa, 